2023 - Reflecting on the most life changing year of my life

As 2023 draws to a close, I wanted to write a post about this year which was the wildest most unexpected year of my life. Beyond my wildest dreams and imaginations. I think that I came upon this scene unexpectedly without a lot of ppl knowing where I came from etc so this post will highlight a bit about that but mostly about gratefulness and gratitude to this year and the ppl who helped me along my journey

The start

At the start of this year, I was nothing. Not in terms of followers but I was a clueless duck in the land of crypto. I tried trading 10-20% swings on huge coins on binance and followed 'TA' and 'macro' experts. I never did on chain.

I have to thank @KaminoCrypto (long before he was famous, I bleieve he also tried trading 10-20% moves on CEX coins like I did), it was his call on $HERA that made me realise the power of on chain and his tweet that said 'on chain is where the money is made, I'm never going back to CEX' that made me pivot full time to onchain.

I changed my whole approach, found gem hunters on twitter that had a successful track record to start following and tried joining every public tg group. I slowly (by copying others) understood the game and worked everyday to get better. I want to thank @Crypto_Shaggy and @8020_h for basically spoon feeding alfa and trades in public tg groups. Great ppl and great alfa sharers (and also kamino in stfx). It was from this I grew my port of 3 figures to 4 figures in those first few months of learning and experimenting. This was truly the hardest time as starting out is always the hardest.

The middle

I then by taking my learnings and grinding through twitter/dexscreener/tg groups managed to get into @TheeGHouse  and @UnidentifiedDao  eventually. I got into these by simply showing the grind, the only member of G House to be given NFT through grinding it out in another group and staying in UDAO. I think UDAO gets so much unnecessary hate but its notorious for being difficult to stay in, if ur there and stay in, I think it means something. I dn't rlly see why others want to hate on the DAO. Thank u to @CryptoDet_  and @Govanisher  for giving me the opportunity to prove myself and being so helpful/kind along my journey. Truly if others knew the effort u guys put in, they wouldnâ€™t sit there hatin like they do and actually try create their own alfa groups.

In these groups, I learnt so much, the way ppl thought. Every single person there taught me something, whether its analysing projects, diff CT accounts, life. I am so grateful for that. One person though I'd like to thank is @Rancune_eth . I donâ€™t know what it is but he took me under his wing and guided me on how to be the best gem finder but also person. I haven't met a gem finder and genuineperson like him in this space. It was also he who motivated me to start posting on twitter and building a brand.

From here I found twitter fun especially at the start, I just posted plays I liked and because I was a small account no one cared. Some things went well some things didn't. I grew the account mostly through banana and olas bullposting as well posting what I truly passionately believed in. I cannot fake who I am and what I believe in and hopefully that shows through my posts.

Now

Looking back on this journey, I skipped a lot of parts and people but those first steps into this world were the hardest and I am most grateful to those that helped me and gave me a chance. From being clueless on 3 figs at the start of the year to an amount only I could dream of and frens in the space as well as understanding how to analyse projects, I feel truly blessed. Thank you for this year, to ppl that helped me, to ppl that inspired me and to my followers who I will always try to deliver alfa for. It was a dream come true and I cannot wait to make next year even better.

